# UI Components

- Use shadcn/ui components as the foundation. Check if a component exists
  in shadcn before building custom.
- Follow the project's design defaults from `memory.md` (minimal, functional,
  warmer tones, intentional color).
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes. No inline styles, no CSS modules.
- Components must be responsive — mobile-first, then scale up.
- Use semantic HTML elements (`nav`, `main`, `section`, `article`).
- Add accessible labels and ARIA attributes where needed.
- Keep components focused — one responsibility per component.
- All clickable elements must have `cursor-pointer`. This includes buttons,
  links, cards, toggles, tabs, and any element with an onClick handler.
